data.chText: （向学校等机构）捐钱，捐赠，资助
data.enText: to give a large sum of money to a school, a college or another institution to provide it with an income

data.chText: 天生赋有，生来具有（某种特性、品质等）
data.enText: to naturally have a particular feature, quality, etc.
She was endowed with intelligence and wit.
to believe or imagine that sb/sth has a particular quality

data.chText: 她认为马库斯具有她所期望的品质。
data.enText: She had endowed Marcus with the qualities she wanted him to possess.
to endow sb with a responsibility

simple_means.memory_skill: en 使… + dow 给予 → 资助；捐赠

means: (向学校等机构)捐钱，捐赠，资助

data.chText: 天生赋有，生来具有（某种特性、品质等）
data.enText: to naturally have a particular feature, quality, etc.
She was endowed with intelligence and wit.
to believe or imagine that sb/sth has a particular quality

example: When she got married, she got dowered

value.def: You say that someone is endowed with a particular desirable ability, characteristic, or possession when they have it by chance or by birth.

example.ex: You are endowed with wealth, good health and a lively intellect.
example.tran: 你生来就拥有财富、健康和活跃的思维。

value.def: If you endow something with a particular feature or quality, you provide it with that feature or quality.

example.ex: Herbs have been used for centuries to endow a whole range of foods with subtle flavours.
example.tran: 数个世纪以来，香草一直被用于给各种食物增添淡淡的香味。

value.def: If someone endows an institution, scholarship, or project, they provide a large amount of money which will produce the income needed to pay for it.

example.ex: The ambassador has endowed a $1 million public-service fellowships program.
example.tran: 大使资助了一项100万美元的公共服务奖学金计划。

value.tran: 资助，捐助(机构、奖学金、项目等)

partsOfSpeech.dec: con 共同 + dit 给予 + ion 表名词 → 共同给出〔前提〕→ 条件
con 加强 + don 给予 + e → 给予〔大度〕→ 原谅
don 给予 + ate 做，造成，使… → 给出去 → 捐赠
don 给予 + or 表人 → 给予的人 → 捐献者
e 出 + dit 给予 → 给出〔好文章〕→ 编辑
en 使… + dow 给予 → 资助；捐赠
extra 向外 + dit 给予 + e → 向外交出〔逃犯〕→ 引渡
par 平等 + don 给予 → 原谅，宽恕
tra〔= trans 转移〕+ dit 给予 + ion 表名词 → 代代相传 → 传统
